# Code Style Guidelines

## TypeScript/JavaScript Style

- Use single quotes for string literals
- Always use optional chaining (`?.`) when accessing object properties
- Always use nullish coalescing (`??`) or default values for potentially undefined values
- Always check array existence before using array methods
- Validate object properties before destructuring

## React Best Practices

- Wrap pure components with `React.memo` to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations or complex object creation
- Use `useCallback` for function props to maintain referential equality
- Specify proper dependency arrays in `useEffect` to prevent infinite loops
- Avoid inline object/array creation in render to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Use proper key props when rendering lists
- Split nested components with closures into separate components

## CSS Guidelines

- Use Tailwind CSS for styling components
- Follow the utility-first approach
- Group related utility classes together